===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|inflation||swelling|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|īnflātiō||expansion", "blowing up}}, from {{m|la|īnflātus}}, the perfect passive participle of {{term|inflo|īnflō|blow into", "expand}}, from {{term|in||into|lang=la}} + {{m|la|flō||blow}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ɪnˈfleɪʃən/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An act, instance of, or state of expansion or increase in size, especially by injection of a gas.
#: ''The '''inflation''' of the balloon took five hours.''
# {{context|economics|lang=en}} An increase in the general level of prices or in the [[cost of living]].
# {{context|economics|lang=en}} A decline in the value of [[money]].
# {{context|economics|lang=en}} An increase in the quantity of [[money]], leading to a devaluation of existing money.
# Undue expansion or increase, as of academic grades.
# {{context|cosmology|lang=en}} An extremely rapid expansion of the universe, theorised to have occurred very shortly after the [[big bang]].

